div.font:
The weight of the discriminator block is a hyperparameter that can be changed manually to train faster and to achieve good results after training.
The authors of the architecture initialize the weights with a mean of 0, and a standard deviation of 0.02 from the normal distribution, and the weights of the generator block's transposed convolutional layers are initialized by default.
It would be interesting to know how the weights of certain layers change for each iteration, and how this affects the discriminator error.
